menu "SPI NAND BDL example configuration"

    config EXAMPLE_FORMAT_IF_MOUNT_FAILED
        bool "Format the flash if mount failed"
        default n
        help
            If set, format_if_mount_failed is true and the volume is formatted when mount fails.

    config EXAMPLE_FORMAT_BEFORE_MOUNT
        bool "Format the volume before mount (explicit mkfs)"
        default n
        help
            If set, the example registers the WL BDL with FatFS diskio, runs esp_vfs_fat_format_drive()
            using the same esp_vfs_fat_mount_config_t (allocation unit, FAT count), then unregisters
            before calling esp_vfs_fat_bdl_mount(). Use this to force a filesystem layout that matches
            your mount_config without relying on format_if_mount_failed.

endmenu
